{"id":14880927,"mediaExerciseId":"6cc00c77-4c26-4125-9038-b0a7566f5232","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612300,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":182,"solutions":[{"id":5958266,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise will determine the four factors of the present value annuity.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/c7ee1d9f270e1aa27ba0b36a0dbe447b/lateximg_large.png","width":968},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/c7ee1d9f270e1aa27ba0b36a0dbe447b/lateximg.png","width":484}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **present value** annuity determines the current value of a specific future amount. It is calculated by considering the future payments from an annuity and following a specified discount rate.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/3636dc9adb686befe03811dd34379b84/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/3636dc9adb686befe03811dd34379b84/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The four components of a present value annuity are the following:\n\n- **Present value** which  refers to the value of the future sum amount of cash.\n\n- **Discount rate** is the rate of return on the investment used to determine the present value.\n\n- **Cash flow per period**  is the amount of cash received for each period.\n\n- **Maturity date** refers to the life of the loan.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/f9bad43e442c766fa85f65cbfc9124cb/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":127,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/6f2e7f19ce834446d1bf921f38395bc4/f9bad43e442c766fa85f65cbfc9124cb/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"02a78007-9ce3-479a-9147-460871727ac9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3},{"id":6355601,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We  need to determine what's required for calculation of annuity present value.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Annuity present value is the current value of the cash flow and is calculated using the following formula:\n\n$$PV_a=C \\times \\left[\\frac{1-\\dfrac{1}{(1+r)^t}}{r}\\right]$$\n\nwhere:\n\n- $C$ is regularly deposited constant amount of cash (predefined as constant per definition of annuity);\n- $r$ is interest rate;\n- $t$ is deposit period (predefined as constant per definition of annuity);\n- $PV_a$ ie. the present value of annuity itself.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Based on the formula, the compositions of an annuity present value are the cash flows, interest rate, deposit period, and the life of the annuity itself.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"74518cde-5683-4868-80cc-fcdd4e95e3c3","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880928,"exerciseName":"2","page":182,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"19be1739-a64e-413d-9959-6ae2dd36e0bd","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-2-19be1739-a64e-413d-9959-6ae2dd36e0bd"},{"id":14880929,"exerciseName":"3","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca7d5541-c02b-421c-883a-c6b32647fe3d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-3-ca7d5541-c02b-421c-883a-c6b32647fe3d"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880926,"exerciseName":"4","page":178,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d9cfbeba-ba09-41d1-8ea5-22390360de8c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-4-d9cfbeba-ba09-41d1-8ea5-22390360de8c"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-1-6cc00c77-4c26-4125-9038-b0a7566f5232"}